sd+xml" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd"/>\n<link rel="license" href="//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"/>\n<link rel="alternate" type="application/atom+xml" title="Wikipedia Atom feed" href="/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&amp;feed=atom"/>\n<link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portal:Bengali_literature"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" />\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="/resources/lib/html5shiv/html5shiv.min.js"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-100 ns-subject page-Portal_Bengali_literature rootpage-Portal_Bengali_literature skin-vector action-view">\t\t<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main">\n\t\t\t<a id="top"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Portal:Bengali literature</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div id="portals-browsebar" class="hlist" style="text-align: center;">\n<dl>\n<dt><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Topics</a></dt>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Culture_and_the_arts" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Culture</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Geography_and_places" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Geography</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Health_and_fitness" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Health</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#History_and_events" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">History</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Mathematics_and_logic" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Mathematics</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Natural_and_physical_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Nature</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#People_and_self" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">People</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Philosophy_and_thinking" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Philosophy</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Religion_and_belief_systems" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Religion</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Society_and_social_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Society</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Technology_and_applied_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Technology</a></dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n<div style="portal-column; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Intro&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Bengali_literature"><big>Bengali literature</big></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><b>Bengali literature</b> (<a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a>: <span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">\xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x82\xe0\xa6\xb2\xe0\xa6\xbe \xe0\xa6\xb8\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb9\xe0\xa6\xbf\xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x8d\xe0\xa6\xaf</span>, <i>Bangla Sahity\xc3\xb4</i>) denotes the body of writings in the <a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali language</a>. The earliest extant work in Bengali literature is the <i><a href="/wiki/Charyapada" title="Charyapada">Charyapada</a></i>, a collection of Buddhist mystic songs dating back to the 10th and 11th centuries. Thereafter, the timeline of Bengali literature is divided into two periods \xe2\x88\x92 medieval (1360-1800) and modern (after 1800).</p>\n<p>Medieval Bengali literature consists of various poetic genres, including Hindu religious scriptures (e.g. <a href="/wiki/Mangalkavya" class="mw-redirect" title="Mangalkavya">Mangalkavya</a>), Islamic epics (e.g. works of <a href="/wiki/Syed_Sultan" title="Syed Sultan">Syed Sultan</a> and <a href="/wiki/Abdul_Hakim_(poet)" title="Abdul Hakim (poet)">Abdul Hakim</a>), translations of <a href="/wiki/Sanskrit" title="Sanskrit">Sanskrit</a>, <a href="/wiki/Arabic" title="Arabic">Arabic</a> and <a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a> texts, <a href="/wiki/Vaishnava" class="mw-redirect" title="Vaishnava">Vaishnava</a> texts (e.g. biographies of <a href="/wiki/Chaitanya_Mahaprabhu" title="Chaitanya Mahaprabhu">Chaitanya Mahaprabhu</a>), and secular texts by Muslim poets (e.g. works of <a href="/wiki/Alaol" title="Alaol">Alaol</a>).</p>\n<p>Novels were introduced to Bengali literature in the mid-19th century. <a href="/wiki/Rabindranath_Tagore" title="Rabindranath Tagore">Rabindranath Tagore</a>, poet, playwright, novelist, painter, essayist, musician, and social reformer, is the best known figure of Bengali literature to the world. He won the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1913. After the post-<a href="/wiki/Partition_of_India" title="Partition of India">partition</a> era, Bengali literature comprises literature of erstwhile <a href="/wiki/East_Pakistan" title="East Pakistan">East Pakistan</a> (modern-day <a href="/wiki/Bangladesh" title="Bangladesh">Bangladesh</a>) and of <a href="/wiki/West_Bengal" title="West Bengal">West Bengal</a>.</p>\n<div style="text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Bengali_literature" title="Bengali literature">more...</a></b></div>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="portal-column; width:100%">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Selected_article/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article">Selected article</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p>The <b>Charyapada</b> (<a href="/wiki/Assamese_language" title="Assamese language">Assamese</a>: <span lang="as" xml:lang="as">\xe0\xa6\x9a\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa7\x8d\xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xaa\xe0\xa6\xa6</span> <i>S\xc3\xb4rzap\xc3\xb4d</i>, <i>Charjyagiti</i>; <a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a>: <span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">\xe0\xa6\x9a\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa7\x8d\xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xaa\xe0\xa6\xa6</span>) is a collection of mystical poems, <a href="/wiki/Songs_of_realization" title="Songs of realization">songs of realization</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Vajrayana" title="Vajrayana">Vajrayana</a> tradition of Buddhism from the <a href="/wiki/Tantra" title="Tantra">tantric</a> tradition in Bengal.</p>\n<p>It was written in an Abahatta that was the common ancestor of Bengali, Assamese, Odia and Maithili between the 8th and 12th centuries and it is said to be the oldest collection of verses written in those languages.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup> A palm-leaf manuscript of the <i>Charyapada</i> was rediscovered in the early 20th century by <a href="/wiki/Haraprasad_Shastri" title="Haraprasad Shastri">Haraprasad Shastri</a> at the Nepal Royal Court Library.<sup id="cite_ref-GuhathakurtaSchendel2013_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-GuhathakurtaSchendel2013-4">[4]</a></sup> The <i>Charyapada</i> was also preserved in the Tibetan Buddhist canon.<sup id="cite_ref-Kv.C3.A6rne2010_5-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kv.C3.A6rne2010-5">[5]</a></sup></p>\nAs songs of realization, the <i>Charyapada</i> were intended to be sung. These songs of realisation were spontaneously composed verses that expressed a practitioner\'s experience of the enlightened state. Miranda Shaw describes how \'songs of realization were an element of the ritual gathering of practitioners in a <a href="/wiki/Ganachakra" title="Ganachakra">ganachakra</a>:\n<blockquote class="templatequote">\n<p>The feast culminates in the performance of tantric dances and music, that must never be disclosed to outsiders. The revellers may also improvise "songs of realization" (<i>caryagiti</i>) to express their heightened clarity and blissful raptures in spontaneous verse.<sup id="cite_ref-6" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup></p>\n</blockquote>\n<div style="text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Charyapada" title="Charyapada">more...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Selected_picture&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_picture"><i>Selected picture</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:652px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Charyapada.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/26/Charyapada.jpg" width="650" height="95" class="thumbimage" data-file-width="650" data-file-height="95" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">Pages from the <a href="/wiki/Charyapada" title="Charyapada">Charyapada</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Selected_biography&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_biography"><i>Selected biography</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><b>Chandidas</b> (<a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a>: <span lang="bn" xml:lang="bn">\xe0\xa6\x9a\xe0\xa6\xa3\xe0\xa7\x8d\xe0\xa6\xa1\xe0\xa7\x80\xe0\xa6\xa6\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb8</span>; born 1408 CE) refers to a medieval poet of <a href="/wiki/Bengal" title="Bengal">Bengal</a> or possibly more than one. Over 1250 poems related to the love of <a href="/wiki/Radha" title="Radha">Radha</a> and <a href="/wiki/Krishna" title="Krishna">Krishna</a> in <a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a> with the <i>bhanita</i> of Chandidas are found with three different sobriquets along with his name, <i><span title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">Ba\xe1\xb8\x8du</span></i>, <i>Dvija</i> and <i>Dina</i> as well as without any sobriquet also. It is not clear whether these <i>bhanita</i>s actually refer to the same person or not. It is assumed by some modern scholars that the poems which are current in the name of Chandidas are actually the works of at least four different Chandidas, who are distinguished from each other by their sobriquets found in the <i>bhanita</i>s. It is also assumed that the earliest of them was Ananta <span title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">Ba\xe1\xb8\x8du</span> Chandidas, who has been more or less identified as a historical figure born in the 14th century in <a href="/wiki/Birbhum_district" title="Birbhum district">Birbhum district</a> of the present-day <a href="/wiki/West_Bengal" title="West Bengal">West Bengal</a> state and wrote the lyrical <i>Srikrishna Kirtan</i> (Songs in praise of <a href="/wiki/Krishna" title="Krishna">Krishna</a>).</p>\n<div style="text-align:right;"><b><a href="/wiki/Chandidas" title="Chandidas">more...</a></b></div>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Selected_poem&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_poem"><i>Selected poem</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center; width: 60%; margin: auto;">\n<tr>\n<th style="width: 33%;"><a href="/wiki/Bengali_language" title="Bengali language">Bengali</a></th>\n<th style="width: 33%;"><a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a> <a href="/wiki/Transliteration" title="Transliteration">transliteration</a></th>\n<th style="width: 33%;"><a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">Word for Word</a> <a href="/wiki/Translation" title="Translation">translation</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\xe0\xa6\x86\xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x8f \xe0\xa6\x97\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xa8 \xe0\xa6\x9b\xe0\xa7\x87\xe0\xa6\xa1\xe0\xa6\xbc\xe0\xa7\x87\xe0\xa6\x9b\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0\n<p>\xe0\xa6\xb8\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xb2 \xe0\xa6\x85\xe0\xa6\xb2\xe0\xa6\x82\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x8b\xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x9b\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x96\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa8\xe0\xa6\xbf \xe0\xa6\x86\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\xb8\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x9c\xe0\xa7\x87\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x85\xe0\xa6\xb9\xe0\xa6\x82\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa5\xa4 \xe0\xa6\x85\xe0\xa6\xb2\xe0\xa6\x82\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x9d\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xaa\'\xe0\xa6\xa1\xe0\xa6\xbc\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbf\xe0\xa6\xb2\xe0\xa6\xa8\xe0\xa7\x87\xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\x86\xe0\xa6\xa1\xe0\xa6\xbc\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb2 \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa7\x87, \xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x8b\xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xa5\xe0\xa6\xbe \xe0\xa6\xa2\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa7\x81\xe0\xa6\x96\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x9d\xe0\xa6\x82\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa5\xa4</p>\n<p>\xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x8b\xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x9b\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\x96\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x9f\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa8\xe0\xa6\xbe \xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa7\x8b\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa6\xbf\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\x97\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xac \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xbe- \xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xb9\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa6\xbf, \xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x8b\xe0\xa6\xae\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\xaa\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xbc\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa6\xe0\xa6\xbf\xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\x9a\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x87 \xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa7\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa5\xa4 \xe0\xa6\x9c\xe0\xa7\x80\xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa6\xa8 \xe0\xa6\xb2\xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xbc\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa6\xa8 \xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xbf \xe0\xa6\xaf\xe0\xa6\xa6\xe0\xa6\xbf \xe0\xa6\xb8\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xb2 \xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\x81\xe0\xa6\xb6\xe0\xa6\xbf \xe0\xa6\x97\xe0\xa6\xa1\xe0\xa6\xbc\xe0\xa6\xbf, \xe0\xa6\x86\xe0\xa6\xaa\xe0\xa6\xa8 \xe0\xa6\xb8\xe0\xa7\x81\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xa6\xe0\xa6\xbf\xe0\xa6\xac\xe0\xa7\x87 \xe0\xa6\xad\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa6\xbf \xe0\xa6\xb8\xe0\xa6\x95\xe0\xa6\xb2 \xe0\xa6\x9b\xe0\xa6\xbf\xe0\xa6\xa6\xe0\xa7\x8d\xe0\xa6\xb0 \xe0\xa6\xa4\xe0\xa6\xbe\xe0\xa6\xb0\xe0\xa5\xa4</p>\n</td>\n<td><i>Amar e gan chhe\xc5\x97echhe tar sh\xc3\xb4kol \xc3\xb4longkar</i>\n<p><i>Tomar kachhe rakhe ni ar shajer \xc3\xb4hongkar</i> <i>\xc3\x94longkar je majhe p\xc3\xb4\xc5\x97e mil\xc3\xb4nete a\xc5\x97al k\xc3\xb4re,</i> <i>Tomar k\xc3\xb4tha \xc4\x91hake je tar mukh\xc3\xb4ro jh\xc3\xb4ngkar.</i> <i>Tomar kachhe kha\xc5\xa3e na mor kobir g\xc3\xb4rbo k\xc3\xb4ra,</i> <i>M\xc3\xb4hakobi, tomar paee dite chai je dh\xc3\xb4ra.</i> <i>Jibon loe j\xc3\xb4ton kori jodi sh\xc3\xb4rol b\xc3\xa3shi go\xc5\x97i,</i> <i>Apon shure dibe bhori s\xc3\xb4kol chhidro tar.</i></p>\n</td>\n<td>My song has put off her adornments.\n<p>She has no pride of dress and decoration. Ornaments would mar our union; they would come between thee and me; their jingling would drown thy whispers. My poet\'s vanity dies in shame before thy sight. O master poet, I have sat down at thy feet. Only let me make my life simple and straight, like a flute of reed for thee to fill with music.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Did_you_know&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know..."><i>Did you know...</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="floatleft"><a href="/wiki/File:Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Rabindranath Tagore unknown location.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg/200px-Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg" width="200" height="265" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg/300px-Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg/400px-Rabindranath_Tagore_unknown_location.jpg 2x" data-file-width="996" data-file-height="1319" /></a></div>\n<p>..that person(pictured) was the first non-<a href="/wiki/Demographics_of_Europe" title="Demographics of Europe">European</a> to win a <a href="/wiki/Nobel_prize" class="mw-redirect" title="Nobel prize">Nobel prize</a>.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #A3BFBF; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: #82D9D9; color: black; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: black"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Bengali_literature/Categories&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: black">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:black;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Categories"><i>Categories</i></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #A3BFBF; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #F5FFFF;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="floatright"><a href="/wiki/File:C_Puzzle.png" class="image" title="Category puzzle"><img alt="Category puzzle" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/C_Puzzle.png/45px-C_Puzzle.png" width="45" height="45" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thum